{
  "doc_id": "61189",
  "text": "In all the studies of ApoE together, there were, in total, 1,353 stroke patients and 1,915 controls. The prevalence of allele e 2 was 7% and 6% for the stroke cases and the control groups, while the prevalence of allele e 4 for the same groups was 12% and 10%, respectively. In the cases and the controls, the prevalence of e 2 e 2 genotype was 2% and 1%, the prevalence of e 4 e 4 genotype was 2% and 1%, and the prevalence of e 3 e 3 genotype was 67% and 72%, respectively. The prevalence of e 2 e 3 genotype among the stroke patients and the healthy controls was both 9%, while for e 2 e 4 genotype it was 2% in both the groups. The e 3 e 4 genotype prevalence was 19% and 15% among the cases and the controls, respectively. The genotype and the allele frequencies of the individual studies are shown in Tables 6 and 7 . Departure of the genotype frequencies from the Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium among controls was observed in four studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] ).",
